===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|drove}}, {{m|enm|drof}}, {{m|enm|draf}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|drāf||action of driving; a driving out, expulsion; drove, herd, band; company, band; road along which cattle are driven}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*draibō||a drive, push, movement, drove}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*dʰreybʰ-||to drive, push}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*dʰer-||cloudy, dirty, muddy}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{m|sco|drave}}, {{m|sco|dreef||drove, crowd}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|dreef||a walkway, wide road with trees, drove}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{m|gmh|treip||a drove}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{m|sv|drev||a drive, drove}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{m|is|dreif||a scattering, distribution}}. More at {{l|en|drive}}.

